{
  "texts": [
    "In the pretraining phase, extensive unlabeled SMILES datasets are used for model training through three different self-supervised pretraining tasks (masking, augmentation and a combination of masking and augmentation).",
    "During the fine-tuning phase, the pretrained Chemformer is tailored to a specific downstream task and further refined.",
    "A multitask learning strategy is utilized in this process to optimize multiple tasks concurrently, such as multiproperty prediction and multigene activity prediction.",
    "In particular, Chemformer has achieved the highest accuracy available on benchmark datasets for direct synthesis and retrosynthesis prediction.",
    "The outcomes for chemical reaction prediction, molecular optimization and property prediction demonstrate the adaptability of Chemformer to various downstream tasks."
  ]
}